<font color="#FF9900">
  Membership Obligations:</font>
</p>

<p>
<font color="#FF9900">
Members are encouraged to group with guild members over non-guild members as much as possible.</font>
</p>

<p>
<font color="#FF9900">
Members will not /random loot amongst themselves. Loot will go to those that need it most. If 
guildmates can not agree on who should get it, then the Master of Arms shall decide. If the 
Master of Arms is unavailable, then the Guild Leader will make the decision.</font> 
</p>

<p>
<font color="#FF9900">
Members will not auction loot off. If you are in a pickup group and win an item you can not use, 
you can pick any guild member to pass it on to, secure in the knowledge that you will receive 
items you need in the same fashion. If nobody in the Guild needs the item (for example, a Paladin 
only weapon, and we have no Paladins) then it can be auctioned off.</font>
<p>

<p>
<font color="#FF9900">
Tradesfolk are free to make a reasonable profit from their craft but are encouraged, as much as 
possible, to sell to guildmates at cost. However, given that it is expensive to build up the 
most desireable of these skills (jewelcraft/smithing/alchemy) selling for a reasonable profit to 
recoup that expense is permitted. Guild members are encouraged to donate cash to your favorite 
jeweler/smithy/alchemist to help them build their skill to a usefull level.</font>
</p>

<hr />

<p>
<font color="#FF9900">
Issues involving these rules should be brought up with the Sgt at Arms or, in cases involving 
loot, the Master of Arms, who will resolve the issue or kick it up to the Guild Leader.</font>

